article.headline: Indiana St. 59, N. Iowa 46
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Gabe Moore scored 21 points and Indiana State dominated the rebounding in a 59-46 victory over Northern Iowa on Monday night. The Sycamores (12-11, 5-8 Missouri Valley Conference) fell behind by 10 points in the first 7 minutes before their advantage off the boards turned the game in their favor. Adam Arnold had nine rebounds and Trent Wurtz and Jay Tunnell grabbed seven boards apiece to lead Indiana State's 35-19 edge. The Panthers (16-8, 7-6) managed only 2 points off second-chance opportunities. The Sycamores took a 27-21 lead at halftime and built the margin to as many as 15 points with a minute to go in the final period. Harry Marshall added 10 points for Indiana State. Northern Iowa was led by Jared Josten and Brooks McKowen with 11 points each.
